article.description: Justin Turner had 25 points and six assists, Demajeo Wiggins added to his nation-leading double-double total and Bowling Green defeated Green Bay 97-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Justin Turner, Demajeo Wiggins lead Bowling Green to victory
article.linkText: Justin Turner, Demajeo Wiggins lead Bowling Green to victory
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio -- Justin Turner had 25 points and six assists, Demajeo Wiggins added to his nation-leading double-double total and Bowling Green defeated Green Bay 97-68 on Saturday. Wiggins, a 6-foot-10 senior forward, picked up his ninth double-double with 12 points and his 19 rebounds increased his nation-leading rebounding average of 12.2. It was the fourth consecutive home win for the Falcons (5-5). Sandy Cohen III had 16 points and five steals for Green Bay (5-4). PJ Pipes had 13 points and ShanQuan Hemphill added 10. Green Bay, which was averaging 86.5 points per game, shot 36.5 percent from the field and made only 9 of 28 3-pointers. Bowling Green never trailed and the score was never tied. The Falcons' largest lead was 35 points at 78-43. Bowling Green had 51 rebounds to Green Bay's 29.
